spring-object-mapper is a thin layer on top of Spring JdbcTemplate for simple object persistence.

It's not an ORM, and will never be one. If you need full blown ORM, this is not what you are looking for.

Features:
    - Mapping POJOs to/from DB objects
    - CRUD operations
    - Support for different DB Dialects
    - Simple query API. DB queries are done with plain old SQL.

Example: 
    https://github.com/jannehietamaki/spring-object-mapper/blob/master/src/test/java/springobjectmapper/Example.java

Maven:

<dependency>
	<groupId>spring-object-mapper</groupId>
	<artifactId>spring-object-mapper</artifactId>
	<version>1.0-SNAPSHOT</version>
</dependency>

<repositories>
	<repository>
		<id>spring-object-mapper-snapshots</id>
		<url>https://github.com/jannehietamaki/maven-repo/raw/master/snapshots</url>		
	</repository>
</repositories>